%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11104518%2FGF0a7mOXEAA12YP.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20One%20in%20every%20100%2C%20and%20one%20in%20every%2085%3A%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20many%20people%2C%20and%20children%2C%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20Gaza%20over%20the%20last%20100%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20therefore%2C%20have%20been%20the%20deadliest%20100%20days%20of%20armed%20conflict%20ever%20in%20the%2021st%20century%2C%20as%20per%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unescwa.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpubs%2Fpdf%2Fwar_on_gaza_twenty_first_centurys_deadliest_100_days-en_0.pdf%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20by%20the%20Economic%20and%20Social%20Commission%20for%20Western%20Asia%2C%20a%20body%20of%2020%20Arab%20countries%20under%20the%20United%20Nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20has%20called%20for%20an%20%E2%80%9Cimmediate%20cessation%20of%20all%20hostilities%E2%80%9D.%20Among%20its%20many%20recommendations%2C%20the%20report%20stressed%20on%20the%20need%20for%20civilians%20to%20be%20protected%2C%20and%20be%20able%20to%20avail%20of%20unrestricted%20access%20to%20humanitarian%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDeadliest%20armed%20conflict%20this%20century%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20on%20Gaza%20by%20Israel%20crossed%20its%20100th%20day%20on%20January%2014.%20The%20war%2C%20which%20began%20on%20October%207%20last%20year%2C%20has%20resulted%20in%20destruction%2C%20displacement%20and%20deaths.%20As%20of%20February%206%20this%20year%2C%2027%2C585%20Palestinians%20have%20lost%20their%20lives%20and%2066%2C978%20have%20been%20injured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20one%20of%20the%20statistics%20in%20the%20recent%20report%20on%20the%20war%20published%20by%20the%20Economic%20and%20Social%20Commission%20for%20Western%20Asia%20(ECSWA).%20This%20body%20under%20the%20United%20Nations%20aims%20to%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20support%20economic%20and%20social%20development%20in%20member%20countries%2C%20and%20promote%20interaction%20and%20cooperation%20between%20them.%20The%20ESCWA%20comprises%2020%20Arab%20countries%3A%20Algeria%2C%20Bahrain%2C%20Egypt%2C%20Iraq%2C%20Jordan%2C%20Kuwait%2C%20Lebanon%2C%20Libya%2C%20Mauritania%2C%20Morocco%2C%20Oman%2C%20the%20State%20of%20Palestine%2C%20Qatar%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20the%20Sudan%2C%20Somalia%2C%20the%20Syrian%20Arab%20Republic%2C%20Tunisia%2C%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20and%20Yemen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20ESCWA%20report%2C%20more%20than%20one%20person%20in%20every%20100%20people%20in%20Gaza%20has%20been%20killed%20in%20just%20100%20days.%20This%20amounts%20to%20240%20deaths%20every%20day.%20The%20rate%20of%20deaths%20%E2%80%9Cexceeds%20that%20of%20any%20other%20armed%20conflict%20in%20the%20twenty-first%20century%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChildren%20the%20worst%20hit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20children%20have%20been%20terribly%20hit.%20Of%20the%2027%2C585%20people%20killed%20in%20Gaza%2C%2012%2C345%20are%20children.%20One%20child%20in%20every%2085%3A%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20many%20children%20have%20died%20here%20during%20the%20100%20days%20so%20far%2C%20per%20the%20report.%20This%2C%20the%20report%20says%2C%20is%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20highest%20rate%20by%20a%20wide%20margin%20when%20compared%20with%20other%20recent%20major%20conflicts%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20has%20called%20for%20an%20%E2%80%9Cimmediate%20cessation%20of%20all%20hostilities%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20predicts%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdestructive%20impacts%20of%20the%20ongoing%20war%20on%20the%20social%2C%20economic%20and%20institutional%20fabric%20of%20the%20State%20of%20Palestine%20will%20severely%20affect%20humanitarian%2C%20development%20and%20recovery%20efforts%20for%20generations%20of%20Palestinians%20to%20come%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20impacts%20will%20only%20intensify%20the%20risk%20of%20future%20violence%2C%20making%20the%20prospect%20of%20renewed%20and%20deadlier%20outbreaks%20more%20likely%20in%20the%20future%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20include%20protecting%20civilians%20and%20civilian%20essential-service%20infrastructure%20and%20ensuring%20unrestricted%20access%20to%20humanitarian%20aid%20(and%20recommends%20that%20aid%20providers%20strengthen%20their%20collaboration%20and%20coordination%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20their%20aid%20is%20effective).%20It%20also%20stressed%20on%20the%20need%20to%20%E2%80%9Crehabilitate%E2%80%9D%20health%20infrastructure%2C%20including%20hospitals%20and%20other%20medical%20facilities%2C%20by%20providing%20them%20with%20fuel%2C%20medicines%2C%20equipment%20and%20human%20resources.%20It%20will%20also%20be%20crucial%20to%20provide%20psychological%20and%20emotional%20support%20to%20traumatised%20people%2C%20and%20particularly%20children%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIsrael%C2%A0intensifies%C2%A0airstrikes%20on%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20Rafah%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%2025%20people%20were%20killed%20as%C2%A0Israeli%C2%A0airstrikes%20pounded%20the%20city%20of%20Rafah%20on%C2%A0Gaza%E2%80%99s%20southern%20border%20overnight%20and%20into%20Saturday%2C%20according%20to%20the%20health%20ministry%20in%20the%20Hamas-controlled%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2024%2F02%2F1146412%5C%22%3Elatest%20news%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20UN%2C%20the%20city%20of%20Rafah%20in%20south%20Gaza%20on%20the%20border%20with%20Egypt%20is%20now%20home%20to%20more%20than%20half%20of%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20population%20of%20more%20than%20two%20million.%20The%20city%20was%20already%20home%20to%20about%202%2C50%2C000%20people.%20Resources%20%E2%80%93%20including%20access%20to%20food%20and%20clean%20water%20%E2%80%93%20are%20dwindling.%20According%20to%20municipal%20authorities%2C%20the%20city%20has%20produced%20the%20equivalent%20of%20a%20year%E2%80%99s%20worth%20of%20garbage%20in%20just%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20Prime%20Minister%C2%A0Benjamin%20Netanyahu%C2%A0directed%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20military%20to%20plan%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cevacuation%20of%20the%20population%20and%20destroying%E2%80%9D%20Hamas%20fighters%20in%20Rafah%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20forces%20have%20already%20carried%20out%20operations%20in%20the%20strip%E2%80%99s%20two%20main%20cities%20%E2%80%94%20Gaza%20City%20and%20Khan%20Younis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plan%20has%20been%20heavily%20criticised%20by%20humanitarians%20and%20some%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20closest%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIsrael%E2%80%99s%20declared%20ground%20offensive%20on%20Rafah%20would%20be%20catastrophic%20and%20must%20not%20proceed%2C%E2%80%9D%20Doctors%20Without%20Borders%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20place%20that%20is%20safe%20in%20Gaza%20and%20no%20way%20for%20people%20to%20leave.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20sense%20of%20growing%20anxiety%2C%20growing%20panic%20in%20Rafah%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Philippe%20Lazzarini%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20UNRWA%20agency.%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20have%20no%20idea%20where%20to%20go.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNo%20war%20can%20be%20allowed%20in%20a%20gigantic%20refugee%20camp%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Jan%20Egeland%2C%20Secretary-General%20of%20the%20Norwegian%20Refugee%20Council%2C%20warning%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbloodbath%E2%80%9D%20if%20Israeli%20operations%20expand%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPalestinian%20president%20Mahmud%20Abbas%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%2C%20which%20administers%20part%20of%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20called%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cblatant%20violation%20of%20all%20red%20lines.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahmoud%20Abbas%20warned%20it%20would%20amount%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Cprelude%20to%20expulsion.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20State%20Department%20also%20said%20it%20does%C2%A0not%20support%20a%20ground%20offensive%20in%20Rafah%2C%20warning%20that%2C%20if%20not%20properly%20planned%2C%20such%20an%20operation%20risked%20%E2%80%9Cdisaster.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGerman%20foreign%20minister%20Annalena%20Baerbock%20has%20warned%20that%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20planned%20offensive%20in%20Rafah%20would%20unleash%20a%20%E2%80%9Chumanitarian%20catastrophe.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%E2%80%9CThe%20emergency%20in%20Rafah%20is%20already%20unbelievable.%201.3%20million%20people%20are%20seeking%20refuge%20from%20the%20fighting%20in%20a%20very%20small%20space%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20wrote%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEU%20foreign%20policy%20chief%20Josep%20Borrell%20warned%20that%20an%20Israeli%20offensive%20on%20Rafah%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20lead%20to%20an%20unspeakable%20humanitarian%20catastrophe%20and%20grave%20tensions%20with%20Egypt.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CResuming%20negotiations%20to%20free%20hostages%20and%20suspend%20hostilities%20is%20the%20only%20way%20to%20avert%20a%20bloodshed%2C%E2%80%9D%20Borrell%20posted%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBritish%20foreign%20secretary%20David%20Cameron%20also%20said%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Cdeeply%20concerned%20about%20the%20prospect%20of%20a%20military%20offensive%20in%20Rafah.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20priority%20must%20be%20an%20immediate%20pause%20in%20the%20fighting%20to%20get%20aid%20in%20and%20hostages%20out%2C%E2%80%9D%20Cameron%20posted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWith%20inputs%20from%20DW.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707628561000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11104518%2FGF0a7mOXEAA12YP.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fgaza-israels-allies-question-rafah-strikes-deadliest-100-days-in-21st-century-says-un-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%2