familiarity%20and%20sensitivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20novel%20opens%20with%20Naren%20Agashe%2C%20who%20decides%20to%20come%20back%20to%20India%20after%20working%20at%20a%20multinational%20in%20the%20US%20because%20of%20the%20economic%20opportunities%20he%20believes%20are%20opening%20up%2C%20and%20because%20an%20isolated%20life%20in%20the%20States%20was%20making%20him%20unhappy.%20He%20is%20joined%20on%20his%20journey%20home%20by%20Amanda%2C%20a%20college%20classmate%20who%20wants%20to%20volunteer%20in%20India.%20Naren%E2%80%99s%20younger%20brother%2C%20Rohit%2C%20is%20an%20aspiring%20film%20producer%20with%20boyish%20charms%20who%20is%20looking%20for%20his%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%E2%80%99s%20perspective%20isn%E2%80%99t%20limited%20to%20the%20three%20of%20them%20%E2%80%93%20it%20grows%20to%20encompass%20their%20friends%2C%20families%20and%20the%20people%20they%20encounter%2C%20including%20Omkar%20Khaire%2C%20a%20filmmaker%20and%20a%20%3Cem%3Ekaryakarta%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20the%20ruling%20right-wing%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERege%20spoke%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%20the%20choices%20she%20made%20in%20her%20book%2C%20how%20its%20central%20theme%20emerged%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYour%20book%20is%20set%20in%20a%20very%20precise%20moment%2C%20right%20after%20the%202014%20elections.%20That%E2%80%99s%20a%20moment%20I%20think%20everyone%20would%20agree%20was%20pivotal%2C%20though%20they%20may%20have%20different%20opinions%20on%20it.%20And%20that%20moment%20still%20feels%20exceedingly%20present%2C%20because%20we%E2%80%99re%20still%20feeling%20the%20impact%20of%20it%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20continuing.%20What%20drew%20you%20to%20this%20as%20the%20setting%20for%20your%20book%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20moment%20might%20be%20precise%2C%20but%20I%20hope%20the%20novel%20feels%20relevant%20to%20a%20much%20longer%20arc.%202014%20brought%20to%20the%20fore%20widescale%20moral%