20curious%20about%20Amanda%20as%20an%20American%20in%20a%20story%20set%20in%20India.%20What%20is%20her%20relevance%20to%20the%20novel%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20character%20was%20an%20occasion%20to%20explore%20a%20certain%20worldview%20and%20dimension%20of%20the%20times.%20At%20the%20start%2C%20Rohit%2C%20Amanda%20and%20Naren%20also%20offered%20a%20useful%20triumvirate%20of%20perspectives%20in%20the%20form%20of%20the%20insider%2C%20the%20outsider%2C%20and%20the%20insider-outsider.%20That%20Amanda%20is%20an%20American%20with%20English%20ancestors%20is%20not%20irrelevant%20because%20the%20dynamic%20between%20East%20and%20West%20has%20shaped%20our%20identity%20for%20centuries.%20Since%20liberalisation%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20more%20taken%20up%20with%20the%20US%20than%20the%20UK.%20A%20lot%20of%20middle-class%20kids%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9990s%20grew%20up%20on%20American%20movies%20and%20music.%20The%20brain%20drain%20to%20Silicon%20Valley%20was%20at%20its%20peak.%20Wealthy%20cousins%20who%20went%20to%20the%20States%20for%20a%20summer%20came%20back%20with%20an%20accent.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20like%20to%20admit%20that%20now.%20There%E2%80%99s%20been%20a%20cultural%20shift%2C%20and%20we%20are%20desperate%20to%20destroy%20the%20white%20gaze%20with%20an%20urgency%20that%20both%20Naren%20and%20Rohit%20suffer.%20But%20there%20is%20a%20person%20on%20the%20other%20side.%20What%20happens%20when%20they%20are%20dehumanised%3F%20Does%20it%20liberate%20us%3F%20To%20explore%20such%20questions%2C%20Amanda%20had%20to%20have%20a%20full%20life.%20It%20also%20felt%20important%20that%20she%20isn%E2%80%99t%20simply%20an%20instrument%20for%20the%20Indians%20to%20know%20themselves%20better.%20The%20novel%20may%20be%20set%20largely%20in%20India%2C%20but%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20about%20India%20alone.%20If%20it%20was%2C%20it%20would%20be%20a%20simpler%20novel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20a%20scene%20in%20the%20book%20where%20all%20the%20characters%20start%20arguing%20about%20politics.%20Fault%20lines%20that%20were%20already%20starting%20to%20show%20come%20out%20starkly%2C%20and%20the%20argument%20ends%20badly.%20Would%20that%20conversation%20have%20looked%20different%20today%3F%20Would%20it%20have%20happened%20at%20all%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20more%20such%20conversations%20at%20the%20time%2C%20I%20think.%20Whether%20it%20was%202014%20in%20India%20or%202016%20in%20the%20US%20or%20Brexit%2C%20several%20democracies%20were%20witnessing%20a%20period%20of%20acute%20polarisation%20at%20the%20level%20of%20friends%20and%20family.%20Suddenly%2C%20whom%20a%20person%20voted%20for%20seemed%20to%20betray%20something%20essential%20about%20their%20character.%20Whether%20or%20not%20this%20is%20true%2C%20those%20of%20us%20who%20came%20of%20age%20then%20will%20remember%20how%20such%20inflection%20points%20made%20us%20aware%20of%20the%20differences%20among%20our%20closest.%20Now%20the%20filters%20come%20on%20earlier.%20A%20college%20student%20recently%20told%20me%20that%20unlike%20the%20characters%20in%20%3Cem%3EQuarterlife%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20he%20would%20not%20make%20friends%20who%20hold%20such%20different%20views%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20There%20are%20subjects%20that%20families%20have%20banned%20at%20dinner%20and%20on%20groups%20online.%20Dialogue%20has%20entirely%20broken%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EYour%20book%20delves%20into%20the%20interiority%20of%20all%20its%20characters%2C%20often%20telling%20us%20what%20is%20happening%20externally%20through%20their%20perspective.%20What%20drew%20you%20to%20this%20exploration%20of%20interiority%20as%20a%20feature%20of%20the%20narrative%3F%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20choice%20was%20instinctive%20at%20first.%20It%20may%20have%20had%20to%20do%20with%20what%20I%20find%20interesting%20about%20people%20or%20the%20form%2C%20since%20no%20medium%20allows%20you%20to%20inhabit%20the%20minute-to-minute%20thoughts%20of%20multiple%20characters%20in%20language%20quite%20like%20the%20novel.%20But%20as%20I%20kept%20at%20it%2C%20I%20also%20found%20the%20technique%20especially%20relevant%20to%20what%20I%20was%20attempting%20with%20this%20particular%20book.%20It%20pushed%20me%20past%20my%20own%20assumptions%20about%20people%20by%20forcing%20me%20to%20understand%20them%20more%20fully%20than%20if%20I%20had%20written%20them%20only%20from%20the%20outside.%20It%20also%20raised%20uncomfortable%20questions%20about%20representation%2C%20the%20tension%20between%20empathy%20and%20judgment%2C%20and%20between%20ethics%20and%20aesthetics%2C%20many%20of%20which%20felt%20relevant%20not%20just%20to%20art%20but%20to%20our%20responsibilities%20and%20moral%20dilemmas%20as%20everyday%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20voice%20changes%20a%20little%20with%20each%20character%E2%80%99s%20perspective.%20In%20places%2C%20Amanda%E2%80%99s%20voice%20comes%20in%20anecdotes%2C%20almost%20like%20diary%20entries%2C%20while%20Naren%E2%80%99s%20feels%20more%20like%20an%20interior%20monologue.%20There%20is%20also%20a%20change%20of%20literary%20form%20and%20the%20number%20of%20voices%20with%20each%20section.%20Did%20that%20come%20naturally%20as%20well%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20grew%20organically%20in%20that%20each%20movement%20was%20a%20response%20to%20the%20last.%20To%20state%20the%20rationale%20for%20every%20gesture%20would%20flatten%20the%20reading%20experience%2C%20but%20I%20can%20share%20something%20my%20editor%20said%20the%20other%20day.%20She%20described%20%3Cem%3EQuarterlife%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20a%20novel%20that%20endlessly%20mushrooms%20outwards.%20Most%20novels%20introduce%20a%20set%20of%20characters%20in%20the%20first%20half%20and%20resolve%20their%20arcs%20in%20the%20second%2C%20but%20in%20%3Cem%3EQuarterlife%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20new%20characters%20keep%20appearing%20in%20even%20the%20final%20chapters%20and%20reference%20still%20others%20beyond.%20Some%20readers%20have%20found%20this%20exasperating.%20I%20suppose%20it%20defies%20the%20usual%20tenets%20of%20storytelling%2C%20but%20frankly%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20see%20myself%20as%20a%20storyteller.%20Everyone%20is%20peddling%20stories%20these%20days%2C%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20celebrities%2C%20politicians%20or%20brands%2C%20and%20there%20is%20something%20violent%20about%20a%20too-tidy%20narrative%20of%20human%20consciousness%20or%20history.%20As%20I%20understand%20it%2C%20the%20novelist%E2%80%99s%20task%20is%20to%20make%20meaning%20of%20the%20ideas%20of%20an%20epoch%20through%20a%20textual%20form%20that%20is%20uniquely%20spacious%20and%20versatile.%20To%20think%20of%20fiction%20as%20anything%20less%20is%20to%20underestimate%20its%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707626243000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11094350%2FProfile-for-the-Wire.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fnot-a-storyteller-an-interview-with-quarterlife-author-devika-rege%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BAs%20I%20understand%20it%2C%20the%20novelist%E2%80%99s%20task%20is%20to%20make%20meaning%20of%20the%20ideas%20of%20an%20epoch%20through%20a%20textual%20form%20that%20is%20uniquely%20spacious%20and%20versatile.%20To%20think%20of%20fiction%20as%20anything%20less%20is%20to%20underestimate%20its%20potential.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fnot-a-storyteller-an-interview-with-quarterlife-author-devika-rege%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Are%20Dalljiet%20Kaur%20and%20Nikhil%20Patel%20headed%20for%20separation%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707625800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107588065%2Cimgsize-68948.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fhindi%2Fare-dalljiet-kaur-and-nikhil-p